Such as betwixt a sealed will, and the things conveighed in the same;
From whence it is, that the names, effects, and properties of the one are
given to the other.



Onely two; to wit, Baptisme, succeeding in the place of Circumcision;
and the Supper of the Lord,The Sacraments of the New Testament. answering to the Passeover, (Rom.
4. 1. Gen. 17. 11, 12. 1 Cor. 10. 1, 2, 3. & 12▪ 13. Matth. 26. 26. & 28. 19.)
By the former, wee have our admission into the true Church of God;
by the latter, wee are nourished and preserved in the Church after our
admission.

Sixthly, lastly and especially, water is a cleansing and a purifying element;
and it resembles the blood of Christ fitly in that, for 1 Joh. 1.
7. The blood of Christ cleanseth us from all sin.
